C

com.nickbenn.onehundred - package com.nickbenn.onehundred
Base package for classes and interfaces making up the implementation of One Hundred.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller - package com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller
Classes responsible for handling command-line options to initialize the system state; presenting visual representations of the system state (as constructed by the classes and interfaces in the com.nickbenn.onehundred.view package); prompting for and accepting user input; and handling user input by invoking appropriate methods on instances of model and view classes.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.model - package com.nickbenn.onehundred.model
Classes and interfaces responsible for managing the internal system state, including validation and processing of moves in the game that may result in state changes.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.model.exception - package com.nickbenn.onehundred.model.exception
Throwable subclasses encapsulating errors that may occur during initialization of the system state and during subsequent processing of state transitions (moves in the game).
com.nickbenn.onehundred.strategy - package com.nickbenn.onehundred.strategy
Abstract and concrete classes declaring and implementing computer strategies for playing the game.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.view - package com.nickbenn.onehundred.view
Classes and interfaces responsible for constructing text-based (in the current implementation) representations of the system state and key transitions.
CommandLineOptions - Class in com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller
Defines several position-independent command-line options, along with the CommandLineOptions.parse(String[]) method for populating corresponding fields from the command line at runtime, and accessor methods to interrogate the resulting option values.
CommandLineOptions() - Constructor for class com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller.CommandLineOptions
Initialize this instance by defining the various options to be recognized by CommandLineOptions.parse(String[]).
ConsoleMain - Class in com.nickbenn.onehundred
Implements entry point for console-mode implementation of "One Hundred", a simple form of the Nim category of mathematical games.
ConsoleSession - Class in com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller
 
ConsoleSession(String[]) - Constructor for class com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller.ConsoleSession
Initializes this instance with the provided args and connects to the standard input device for subsequent user interaction.
ConsoleSolitaireReferee - Class in com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller
Manages user interaction—with corresponding updates to the game state—through completion of a single solitaire (user against computer) game.
ConsoleSolitaireReferee.Builder - Class in com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller
Concrete implementation of the Builder pattern used for constructing instances of ConsoleSolitaireReferee.
